to the editor tom nesi 's eloquent catalog of the pain and sorrow of his wife 's death provides a cautionary tale op ed june 5 cancers and other life threatening chronic illnesses regularly leave patients caretakers and doctors with decisions based on relative risks that are difficult or impossible to quantify accurately as the husband of a leading advocate for people with lung cancer who is also a long term cancer patient i am privy to many stories that provide balance to the nesis ordeal the medication iressa which mr nesi mentions has provided many months of high quality extended life to many patients whom i am aware of such drugs like many new therapies work well in some groups of patients but not in others and continued study is needed to determine which treatments give desperate patients actual hope false hope or no hope at all james parles md setauket ny june 5 2003

